gomodel:SYNGO_4123  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig1A: Immunocytochemistry shows that immunoreaction product of endogenous APPL1 colocalises with presynaptic synaptic vesicle marker SV2 (marked by white arrows). Almost 90% of the SV2 clusters colocalise with APPL1 in excitatory hippocampal neurons.\n\n18/01/2021: The paper does not comment on the specificity of the antibody used.. Experimental description: Low density hippocampal neuronal cultures were prepared and maintained as previously described (Goslin et al., 1998). The information of species was retrieved from Goslin et al., 1998." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2916-7616" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2021-01-18" ;
